Would I benefit from a sql editor; ie a tool that lets me type out queries? Google postgres sql editor
pgadmine does a lot of this, and many other things. pgadmin is described as the #1 GUI tool used with postgres. 
, it's probably vital to be used in professional sql work.

Tip: SUM(CASE WHEN) can be useful when you need multiple totals:"
10. From the `events` table, write a query that gets the total number of buys, likes and shares for each meal id. 
_Extra_: To avoid having to do this as three separate queries you can do the count of the number of buys like this: `SUM(CASE WHEN event='bought' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)`.
"
